    "summary": "Alexander R. Scholtens Weert is since 2012 the Managing Director of De Sayter BV. De Sayter is an estate on a 40 hectares private island in Friesland The Netherlands. The estate specializes in organizing high end weddings and corporate meetings. Sustainability and decreasing the environmental footprint are key factors for the organization. De Sayter has been awarded the Green Key Gold Award for  over 6 consecutive years. The Green Key award is the leading standard for excellence in the field of environmental responsibility and sustainable operation within the tourism industry. Since 2015 De Sayter is although private an integrated part of the National Park \u201c De Oude Venen\u201d.\nAlexander started his career in Pharmaceutical sales with Eli Lilly and Company. Worked for Hoffman La Roche as Business Unit Director Benzodiazepines. His major achievement was introducing Dormicum (midazolam) on the Intensive Care Units. For MiniMed Sylmar, a California based Medical Device Company he managed for 8 years the Companies start- ups in The Benelux and in the major parts of Europe. Setting up a European Headquarter in Brussels he assisted in moving the business to Medtronic. With his own Company ARSW Consultants specialized in Interim and Crisis Management he achieved major goals in restructuring several major companies, although with a focus on Pharmaceutical Companies (e.g.Almirall Prodes Pharma). Before becoming the Managing Director of De Sayter, Alexander worked for over 8 years for Alliance Pharmaceutical as Vice President International. In that position he appointed over 24 distributors World Wide. In China he did set up a Joint Venture between the UK based company and a Chinese Partner with his main offices in Guangzhou and Hong Kong and was member of the Board of Directors. Currently  Alexander is on the Board of several small and medium sized companies in The Netherlands.",
